.TE
.VL  
.LI "\*LXmNsliderVisual\*O"
Specifies the visual representation of the slider.
This can take on the values XmETCHED_LINE, the default; XmSHADOWED,
meaning there is no single etched line across the center of the slider;
and XmFLAT_FOREGROUND, meaning there is no etched line and there are
no shadows on the edges of the slider.
.LI "\*LXmNslidingMode\*O"
Specifies the way the slider shows the current value.
This can take on the values XmSLIDER, the default, meaning that the
slider moves back and forth within the trough to show the value; and
XmTHERMOMETER, meaning that the slider is anchored to one end of the
trough and it grows and shrinks to show the value.
.LI "\*LXmNeditable\*O"
Specifies whether the scale widget acts upon user input.
Setting this to False makes the scale widget insensitive to user input
but not greyed out as if XmNsensitive was used.
